4	-- =============================================================================
5	-- Authors:					Thomas B. Preusser
6	--									Steffen Koehler
7	--									Martin Zabel
8	--
9	-- Entity:					FIFO, independent clocks (ic), first-word-fall-through mode
10	--
11	-- Description:
12	-- -------------------------------------
13	-- Independent clocks meens that read and write clock are unrelated.
14	--
15	-- This implementation uses dedicated block RAM for storing data.
16	--
17	-- First-word-fall-through (FWFT) mode is implemented, so data can be read out
18	-- as soon as ``valid`` goes high. After the data has been captured, then the
19	-- signal ``got`` must be asserted.
20	--
21	-- Synchronous reset is used. Both resets may overlap.
22	--
23	-- ``DATA_REG`` (=true) is a hint, that distributed memory or registers should be
24	-- used as data storage. The actual memory type depends on the device
25	-- architecture. See implementation for details.
26	--
27	-- ``*STATE_*_BITS`` defines the granularity of the fill state indicator
28	-- ``*state_*``. ``fstate_rd`` is associated with the read clock domain and outputs
29	-- the guaranteed number of words available in the FIFO. ``estate_wr`` is
30	-- associated with the write clock domain and outputs the number of words that
31	-- is guaranteed to be accepted by the FIFO without a capacity overflow. Note
32	-- that both these indicators cannot replace the ``full`` or ``valid`` outputs as
33	-- they may be implemented as giving pessimistic bounds that are minimally off
34	-- the true fill state.
35	--
36	-- If a fill state is not of interest, set *STATE_*_BITS = 0.
37	--
38	-- ``fstate_rd`` and ``estate_wr`` are combinatorial outputs and include an address
39	-- comparator (subtractor) in their path.
40	--
41	-- Examples:
42	-- - FSTATE_RD_BITS = 1: fstate_rd == 0 => 0/2 full
43	--                       fstate_rd == 1 => 1/2 full (half full)
44	--
45	-- - FSTATE_RD_BITS = 2: fstate_rd == 0 => 0/4 full
46	--                       fstate_rd == 1 => 1/4 full
47	--                       fstate_rd == 2 => 2/4 full
48	--                       fstate_rd == 3 => 3/4 full
