12	-- especially useful for smaller FIFO sizes, which can be implemented in LUT
13	-- storage on some devices (e.g. Xilinx' SRLs). Only a single read pointer is
14	-- maintained, which determines the number of valid entries within the
15	-- underlying shift register.
16	--
17	-- The specified depth (``MIN_DEPTH``) is rounded up to the next suitable value.
